Define the gluing function, $\sg_H: \{(\Fa,\si)\in \CM(H)\times \FX_{d,k}(H) ~:~ \si\in\partial \Phi(\Fa)\} \to \CM(H)$ as follows: Note that for $\Fa=[K_{\widehat{J}}g]_H$ and $\si\in \partial\Phi(\Fa)$, there exists a unique $l\in J$, such that $\si = \Phi([K_{\widehat{J\setminus l}}g]_H)$. Then, set
	\begin{equation}
		\sg_H([K_{\widehat{J}}g]_H,\si) = [K_{\widehat{J\setminus l}}g]_H,
