Let \mbox{($\cM$, $f_1$, $\hdots$, $f_k$)} be an $\bm{n}$-magma, where $\bm{n} = (n_1, \hdots, n_k)$. A \textbf{norm} is a map $\norm{\cdot}: \cM \rightarrow \mathbb{N}$ that satisfies the \textbf{super-additive} conditions:
\begin{enumerate}
