[Coalgebra]\label{defn:coalgebra}
  A coalgebra $\cC$ over a field $\KK$ is a $\KK$-linear space endowed with two algebra homomorphisms: 
  \begin{itemize}
  \item a coproduct $\Delta :\cC\to\cC\otimes\cC$ satisfying the \emph{coassociativity} condition:
    \begin{align}
      \forall\Gamma\in\cC,\,(\Delta\otimes\id)\circ\Delta(\Gamma)=&(\id\otimes \Delta)\circ\Delta(\Gamma),\label{eq:coasso}
    \end{align}
  \item a counit $\veps :\cC\to\KK$ satisfying:
    \begin{align}
      \forall \Gamma\in\cC,\,(\veps\otimes\id)\circ\Delta(\Gamma)=&\Gamma=(\id\otimes\veps)\circ\Delta(\Gamma).    \end{align}
  \end{itemize}

