	Given $p,p'\in\mathcal P^{\circ\bullet}_{2,\mathrm{nb}}$ and sectors $S$ in $p$ and $S'$ in $p'$, we number the points in $\inte (S)$ and $\inte (S')$ with respect to the cyclic order. We say that $(p,S)$ and $(p',S')$ are \emph{equivalent} if the following four conditions are met:
