		\item The same normalized colors occur in the same order in $S$ and $S'$.
		\item For all $i$, the $i$-th point of $S$ belongs to a block crossing $\partial S$ in $p$ if and only if the $i$-th point of $S'$ belongs to a block crossing $\partial S'$ in $p'$. 
		\item For all $i,j$, the $i$-th and $j$-th points of $S$ form a block in $p$ if and only if the $i$-th and $j$-th points of $S'$ form a block in $p'$.
