\label{def.exceptional}
Let $H$ be a separated labeled hypergraph. A pair of two odd cycles $C_1$ and $C_2$ in $H$ is called an \emph{exceptional} pair if the following conditions are satisfied:
\begin{enumerate}
\item $C_1$ and $C_2$ do not share any vertices nor edges;
\item for $i=1,2$, all but one edges of $C_i$ are 1-dimensional and the remaining edge is a simple edge;
\item the two (possibly) higher dimensional edges of $C_1$ and $C_2$ are connected by at least an edge that does not contain any vertices of $C_1$ and $C_2$;
\item $H$ does not have any edge that contains an odd number of vertices from $C_1$ and $C_2$.
\end{enumerate}

