\begin{equation}
\mu_k[q_f,q_s,q_t]=\begin{cases}
[q_s,q_s \oplus q_t,q_t] & \text{if  }  k=f \\
[q_f,q_f \ominus q_t,q_t] & \text{if  }  k=s \\
[q_f,q_f \oplus q_s,q_s] & \text{if  }  k=t 
\end{cases}
\end{equation}  
In view of Lemma \ref{Farey decomposition} we have that the mutation is an involution, \ie we have $\mu_k\mu_k[q_f,q_s,q_t]=[q_f,q_s,q_t]$ for each $k$.

