		\item For all bases $B$ of $M$, $x \notin B$, there is a basis $B'$ of $N$ with $B' \subseteq B$ and such that $\{y: (B'-y)\cup x \in \mathcal{B}(N)\} \subseteq \{y: (B-y)\cup x \in \mathcal{B}(M)\}$. %{\color{green} Strangely, Oxley doesn't mention this characterisation. White does, but doesn't prove anything. So I'm not sure what to do with the reference here.}
