Given face posets of regular CW complexes $\Pi$ and $\widehat{\Pi}$, we say that $\widehat{\Pi}$ is a \emph{subdivision} of $\Pi$ if there exists a surjective, order preserving map $\phi : \widehat{\Pi} \rightarrow \Pi$ such that for all $F \in \Pi$ the following conditions hold:

\begin{enumerate}
\item $\widehat{F} := \phi^{-1}([\widehat{0}, F])$ is a CW complex of the same dimension as $F$.
\item $\phi^{-1}(F)$ consists of all the interior cells of $\widehat{F}$.
\item $|F| = |\widehat{F}|$
\end{enumerate}

