Let $S$ be a totally ordered idempotent semifield.
	A \emph{tropical Pl\"ucker vector} of rank $d$ on ground set $E$
	is a nonzero vector $w \in S^{\binom{E}{d}}$ satisfying the \emph{tropical Pl\"ucker relations}:
	for any $J \in \binom{E}{d+1}$ and $K \in \binom{E}{d-1}$,
	\begin{equation*}
		\sum_{i \in J - K} w_{J-i}w_{K+i} = \sum_{i \in J-K, i \neq j} w_{J-i}w_{K+i}
	\end{equation*}
	for all $j \in J-K$.

