The \emph{tropical semifield} on a finite family of variables $u_j,\ j \in J$, is the abelian group (written multiplicatively) $\text{Trop}(u_j: j \in J)$ freely generated by the $u_j,\ j \in J$. It is endowed with an auxiliary addition~$\oplus$ defined by
\begin{equation}
\label{eq:tropical-addition}
\prod_j u_j^{a_j} \oplus \prod_j u_j^{b_j} =
\prod_j u_j^{\min (a_j, b_j)} \,.
\end{equation}
